04133nam a22006255i 9780520974326DE-B159720240306124542.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t20202020cau    fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)1158140190  a97805209743267 a10.1525/97805209743262doi  a(DE-B1597)551344  a(OCoLC)1110672758  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 4aUG1242.D7bZ85 2020eb 7aSOC0510002bisacsh04a358.4/242231 aZulaika, Joseba, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aHellfire from Paradise Ranch :bOn the Front Lines of Drone Warfare /cJoseba Zulaika. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (296 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPrologue: Slaughterhouse-359 -- t1. The Real: Home of the Hunters -- t2. Fantasy and the Art of Drone Assassination -- t3. Drone Wars Returning from the Future -- t4. Trauma: The Killer as Voyeur -- t5. Resistance: A Harsh and Dreadful Love -- tEpilogue: Obama’s Troy: Kill Me a Son -- tAcknowledgments -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn this intimate and innovative work, terror expert Joseba Zulaika examines drone warfare as manhunting carried out via satellite. Using Creech Air Force Base near Las Vegas as his center of study, he interviews drone operators as well as resisters to the war economy of the region to expose the layers of fantasy on which counterterrorism and its self-sustaining logic are grounded. Hellfire from Paradise Ranch exposes the terror and warfare of drone killings that dominate our modern military. It unveils the trauma drone operators experience, in part due to their visual intimacy with their victims, and explores the resistance to drone killings in the same apocalyptic Nevada desert where nuclear testing, pacifist militancy, and Shoshone tradition overlap. Stunning and absorbing, Zulaika offers a richly detailed account of how we continue to manufacture, deconstruct, and perpetuate terror.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDrone aircraftxMoral and ethical aspectszUnited States. 0aTerrorismxPrevention. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Violence in Society.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520974326?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520974326423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520974326/original  a978-3-11-069041-5  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-SEWb2020